{"title_page": "Kadir Has University", "text_new": "{{Infobox university|\n|name= Kadir Has University\n|native_name = Kadir Has \u00dcniversitesi\n|image       = KadirHasUniversity.JPG\n|caption     = Kadir Has University's main building in Cibali, Istanbul\n|established = 1997\n|type        = [[Private university]]\n|staff       =\n|president   = Prof. Dr. Mustafa Ayd\u0131n\n|faculty     =\n|students    = \n|city        = [[Istanbul]]\n|country     = [[Turkey]]\n|campus      = Cibali Bah\u00e7elievler, [[Selimpa\u015fa]]\n|affiliations =\n|website= http://www.khas.edu.tr/\n}}\n\n<!--  Commented out because image was deleted: [[Image:Kadir-Has-University.jpg|right|thumb|250px|KHU from one of its student's eye.]] -->\n[[File:Kadir Has \u00dcniversitesi.JPG|thumb|Kadir Has University's [[Selimpa\u015fa]] campus. ]]\n'''Kadir Has University''' ('''KHU''' or as mostly preferred by its students '''KHAS''') is a university in [[Fatih]], [[Istanbul]].<ref>[https://www.khas.edu.tr/en Home]. Kadir Has University. Retrieved on 9 July 2019. \"Cibali Mah. Kadir Has Cad. Fatih / \u0130STANBUL 34083\"</ref>\n\nIt was founded in 1997. A private university, it has seven faculties, Engineering, Sciences and Humanities, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Communication, Law and Fine Arts, as well as its several vocational schools, and is dedicated to becoming a leader in educational and cultural fields in Turkey, as well as establishing itself as an international center for research and scientific development. Prof. Mustafa Ayd\u0131n is the rector of the university.\n\n== History ==\nThe university was founded by the [[Kadir Has Foundation]], established by the late industrialist and philanthropist [[Kadir Has]].\n \nThe university's central campus is located by the [[Golden Horn]] in Cibali, [[Fatih]], the capital district of [[\u0130stanbul]], on the European side of the city. The building was originally a tobacco factory, erected in 1884 by the Istanbul-based [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] [[Armenians|Armenian]] [[architect]] [[Hovsep Aznavur]].<ref>Tigran Khzmalyan. [https://5165news.com/nota-bene/armenian-architects-of-istanbul-online-exhibition-\u057d\u057f\u0561\u0574\u0562\u0578\u0582\u056c\u056b-\u0570\u0561\u0575-\u0573\u0561\u0580\u057f\u0561\u0580\u0561\u057a\u0565\u057f\u0576\u0565/ Armenian Architects of Istanbul: Online Exhibition]{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, March 27, 2015</ref> The factory was used for nearly seventy years by [[TEKEL]] the state tobacco producers. It then fell in disrepair due to the lack of maintenance and eventually was abandoned. It wasn't until the late 1990s when the Kadir Has Foundation came up with the idea to turn this desolated factory building into a university, taking a twenty-nine year lease from Tekel in 1997. After four years of restoration, the university was officially opened on 30 December 2002. The building has over 35.000m<sup>2</sup> of indoor space plus grounds.\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2003 Kadir Has University won the [[Europa Nostra|Europa Nostra Award]] for the beautiful restoration of an historical place. After this huge success, again with the same aim, Kadir Has Charity Foundation bought the C block of the building from TEKEL also and started the restoration of this block which is planned to finish in November 2006.\n\nKadir Has University itself is the sponsor of a number of awards including:\n* a promising scientist award which in 2011 was given to Dr [[Ataman \u015eend\u00f6l]] of the [[University of Zurich]] Institute of Molecular Life Sciences. \n* an achievement award, given to Professor [[Erdal Ar\u0131kan]] of [[Bilkent University]], Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering for a paper on the [[Shannon limit]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of universities in Turkey]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Kadir Has University}}\n* [http://www.khas.edu.tr/ Official Website of Kadir Has University]\n* [http://www.khasmed.com/ Kadir Has University Graduates Club]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080418112742/http://lib.khas.edu.tr/ Library of Kadir Has University]\n{{Fatih}}\n{{Universities and colleges in Istanbul}}\n{{Universities in Turkey}}\n\n{{coord|41|03|08|N|28|22|50|E|region:TR_type:edu|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Istanbul]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Fatih]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Silivri]]\n[[Category:Kadir Has University| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox University|\n|name= Kadir Has University\n|native_name = Kadir Has \u00dcniversitesi\n|image       = KadirHasUniversity.JPG\n|caption     = Kadir Has University's main building in Cibali, Istanbul\n|established = 1997\n|type        = [[Private university]]\n|staff       =\n|president   = Prof. Dr. Mustafa Ayd\u0131n\n|faculty     =\n|students    = \n|city        = [[Istanbul]]\n|country     = [[Turkey]]\n|campus      = Cibali Bah\u00e7elievler, [[Selimpa\u015fa]]\n|affiliations =\n|website= http://www.khas.edu.tr/\n}}\n\n<!--  Commented out because image was deleted: [[Image:Kadir-Has-University.jpg|right|thumb|250px|KHU from one of its student's eye.]] -->\n[[File:Kadir Has \u00dcniversitesi.JPG|thumb|Kadir Has University's [[Selimpa\u015fa]] campus. ]]\n'''Kadir Has University''' ('''KHU''' or as mostly preferred by its students '''KHAS''') is a university in [[Fatih]], [[Istanbul]].<ref>[https://www.khas.edu.tr/en Home]. Kadir Has University. Retrieved on 9 July 2019. \"Cibali Mah. Kadir Has Cad. Fatih / \u0130STANBUL 34083\"</ref>\n\nIt was founded in 1997. A private university, it has seven faculties, Engineering, Sciences and Humanities, Economics and Administrative Sciences, Communication, Law and Fine Arts, as well as its several vocational schools, and is dedicated to becoming a leader in educational and cultural fields in Turkey, as well as establishing itself as an international center for research and scientific development. Prof. Mustafa Ayd\u0131n is the rector of the university.\n\n== History ==\nThe university was founded by the [[Kadir Has Foundation]], established by the late industrialist and philanthropist [[Kadir Has]].\n \nThe university's central campus is located by the [[Golden Horn]] in Cibali, [[Fatih]], the capital district of [[\u0130stanbul]], on the European side of the city. The building was originally a tobacco factory, erected in 1884 by the Istanbul-based [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] [[Armenians|Armenian]] [[architect]] [[Hovsep Aznavur]].<ref>Tigran Khzmalyan. [https://5165news.com/nota-bene/armenian-architects-of-istanbul-online-exhibition-\u057d\u057f\u0561\u0574\u0562\u0578\u0582\u056c\u056b-\u0570\u0561\u0575-\u0573\u0561\u0580\u057f\u0561\u0580\u0561\u057a\u0565\u057f\u0576\u0565/ Armenian Architects of Istanbul: Online Exhibition]{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, March 27, 2015</ref> The factory was used for nearly seventy years by [[TEKEL]] the state tobacco producers. It then fell in disrepair due to the lack of maintenance and eventually was abandoned. It wasn't until the late 1990s when the Kadir Has Foundation came up with the idea to turn this desolated factory building into a university, taking a twenty-nine year lease from Tekel in 1997. After four years of restoration, the university was officially opened on 30 December 2002. The building has over 35.000m<sup>2</sup> of indoor space plus grounds.\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2003 Kadir Has University won the [[Europa Nostra|Europa Nostra Award]] for the beautiful restoration of an historical place. After this huge success, again with the same aim, Kadir Has Charity Foundation bought the C block of the building from TEKEL also and started the restoration of this block which is planned to finish in November 2006.\n\nKadir Has University itself is the sponsor of a number of awards including:\n* a promising scientist award which in 2011 was given to Dr [[Ataman \u015eend\u00f6l]] of the [[University of Zurich]] Institute of Molecular Life Sciences. \n* an achievement award, given to Professor [[Erdal Ar\u0131kan]] of [[Bilkent University]], Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering for a paper on the [[Shannon limit]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of universities in Turkey]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Kadir Has University}}\n* [http://www.khas.edu.tr/ Official Website of Kadir Has University]\n* [http://www.khasmed.com/ Kadir Has University Graduates Club]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080418112742/http://lib.khas.edu.tr/ Library of Kadir Has University]\n{{Fatih}}\n{{Universities and colleges in Istanbul}}\n{{Universities in Turkey}}\n\n{{coord|41|03|08|N|28|22|50|E|region:TR_type:edu|display=title}}\n\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Istanbul]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Fatih]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Silivri]]\n[[Category:Kadir Has University| ]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kadir_Has_University"}
